insert blog "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
===========================================================

NAME
----

insert blog - Store basic site info in the blogs table.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Store basic site info in the blogs table.

This function creates a row in the wp\_blogs table and returns the new
blog's ID. It is the first step in creating a new blog.

USAGE
-----

` <?php insert_blog( $domain, $path, $site_id ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$domain` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The domain of the new site.
    Default: *None*

 `$path` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The path of the new site.
    Default: *None*

 `$site_id` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Unless you're running a multi-network install, be sure
    to set this value to 1.
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(int)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   The ID of the new row

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [MU](/Version_MU "Version MU")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`insert_blog()` is located in `wp-includes/ms-functions.php`

